{"id":836451810,"question_id":345,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1 year, 7 months","timestamp":1667528396,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"4 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/836451810/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Reverse Vowels of a String","memory":"42.6 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public String reverseVowels(String s) {\n        Set<Character> set = new HashSet<>();\n        set.add('a');\n        set.add('e');\n        set.add('i');\n        set.add('o');\n        set.add('u');\n        set.add('A');\n        set.add('E');\n        set.add('I');\n        set.add('O');\n        set.add('U');\n        \n        int st=0, ed=s.length()-1;\n        \n       // \"a.b,.\"\n        // ..b,a\n           \n        \n        \n        \n        char[] arr = s.toCharArray();\n        \n        while(st<ed){\n            \n            while(!set.contains(s.charAt(st))&&st<s.length()-1 )\n                st++;\n            \n             while(!set.contains(s.charAt(ed)) && ed>0  )\n                ed--;\n            \n            if(st<ed){\n                char temp = arr[st];\n                arr[st]= arr[ed];\n                arr[ed]=temp;\n                st++;\n                ed--;  \n            }\n            \n            // System.out.println( new String(arr));\n            \n        }\n        \n        return new String(arr);\n        \n        \n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"reverse-vowels-of-a-string","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
